channel.title: Calypso
channel.description:
[center][u][b]Server Information[/b][/u]
[b]Calypso[/b] is a Server being developed by me and only me. Were trying to sustain as much respect as possible and a huge Community. Calypso has only been developed for atleast 1-2 weeks and is developing quite quickly. Were trying to be at the top, we can do this by; keeping our code clean, effcient and wisely detecting those memory leaks, we also like cutting out those none-used proccescors to stop the EventManager over-flowing.
[u][b]About me[/b][/u]
My name is James, i'm 15 years old. I've only joined this RuneScapePrivateServer Community today and none other. I've been learning/programming Java for around 2-3 years so i'm pretty experienced but I still have alot to learn as i'm sure even the proffessionals do as well.
Yes, I know there's hardly any information, more is coming soon!

item.dc:creator: @Ix_Soulcist_xI Soulcist
item.description:
@Ix_Soulcist_xI wrote:

X Entinity X has taken the words from me once again, and I will have to agree with the whole 562 maps and stuff. It’s shameful that the 317 revision is being ruined with mapdata that the 317 revision shouldn’t have, at first I thought it would be amazing. However, my mind has changed about that, and I think people should keep maps to the 508 + revision, in their own place.

Nevertheless, I do believe this isn’t that bad for having such maps, and hope to not be disappointed. Good luck mate, hope this is successful.

Read full topic

item.title: Calypso
item.dc:creator: @X_Entinity_X X Entinity X
item.description:
@X_Entinity_X wrote:

[quote=“Cres, post:4, topic:381771”][quote author=Agent Jugz link=topic=477581.msg3494345#msg3494345 date=1297193030]
Thanks. I’ve had a roam around and I don’t see alot from scratch other then basic networking, combat and so on.
This isn’t Destination Pking or whatever it’s called.
[/quote]

When people write a whole base from scratch , you know they are pro’s , we have a few of them here , and no i’m not a pro , i just try to expertise in the 317 PI base for a while.
I do have plans for making a 474 from scratch when i get more experienced with java ( swing , imageicons etc , i’m taking lessons xD )
again , GL , ignore flamers / haters , if you managed to do this all in 2 weeks , i’m sure you will get this to a very nice base in no time =D[/quote]

Just because someone can write a base from scratch it doesn’t mean their “Pro”, you just need to learn Java, its concept and how it works overall, if you want more learning experience I suggest useing http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/index.html before moving onto 474. Before all of this, get comfortable with what your doing with Project Insanity or Delta.

@Topic - Good luck, it’s coming along quite well although the concept of RSPS’s are to go back not forward, so I suggest removing “Loading 562/508 data”.
